58
00:02:35,770 --> 00:02:36,670
overheating.

59
00:02:36,736 --> 00:02:39,488
If you have experience in making handmade soap,

60
00:02:39,744 --> 00:02:43,002
you might realize that after filling the mold with soap for 30 minutes to 1 hour

61
00:02:43,102 --> 00:02:47,168
the mold container will feels hot.

62
00:02:47,424 --> 00:02:50,752
This is because the soap continues to heat up during saponification.

63
00:02:51,008 --> 00:02:53,568
and if the temperature gets too high,

64
00:02:53,824 --> 00:02:55,366
it will cause Soap Volcano.

65
00:02:55,872 --> 00:02:58,432
The soap is enclosed within the mold

66
00:02:58,688 --> 00:02:59,968
where heat can only escape via the top surface.

67
00:03:00,224 --> 00:03:01,865
So the soap usually cracks

68
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:03,296
on the top surface.

69
00:03:03,552 --> 00:03:06,364
So what are the other reasons that cause overheating

70
00:03:06,397 --> 00:03:08,416
leading to Soap Volcano?

71
00:03:08,928 --> 00:03:10,309
There are 4 main reasons,

72
00:03:10,309 --> 00:03:13,280
Firstly, the temperature of lye solution and oils was too high during mixing.

73
00:03:13,536 --> 00:03:16,864
Secondly, the mold you are using has very good heat insulating properties.

74
00:03:17,376 --> 00:03:17,888
Thirdly,

75
00:03:18,144 --> 00:03:22,194
you put the soap in places with thermal insulation after it is molded.

76
00:03:22,496 --> 00:03:24,327
For instance, cooler box or oven.

77
00:03:24,527 --> 00:03:28,128
Lastly, you used additives that produce heat naturally.

78
00:03:28,384 --> 00:03:30,176
For example, additives that contain protein,

79
00:03:30,432 --> 00:03:33,391
including cow milk, goat milk, breastmilk and soy milk.

80
00:03:33,391 --> 00:03:34,892
And high natural sugar ingredients,

81
00:03:34,892 --> 00:03:36,064
such as honey.

82
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:38,099
Additives that contain alcohol

83
00:03:38,099 --> 00:03:40,989
that can be found in the popular beer and wine soaps

84
00:03:41,324 --> 00:03:43,190
and some fragrance oils or essential oils

85
00:03:43,257 --> 00:03:45,024
can also cause the temperature of soap to rise.

86
00:03:45,536 --> 00:03:48,096
Based on my previous experience,

87
00:03:48,352 --> 00:03:52,960
most floral fragrance oils or essential oils  will cause the rise in temperature of soap.

88
00:03:53,216 --> 00:03:56,288
But of course it is not only limited to floral essential oils or fragrance oils,

89
00:03:56,544 --> 00:04:00,640
other essential oils or fragrance oils might also cause the temperature to rise.

90
00:04:01,408 --> 00:04:04,686
But there are countless of essential oils and fragrance oils in the market

91
00:04:04,952 --> 00:04:06,528
and they have complicated ingredients,

92
00:04:06,784 --> 00:04:08,851
so I cannot list them out one-by-one in this video.

93
00:04:09,344 --> 00:04:12,135
Plus I am not a professional perfumer or fragrance expert.

94
00:04:12,135 --> 00:04:15,488
I can only share my knowledge based on my past experience,

95
00:04:15,744 --> 00:04:19,016
so feel free to comment down below if you have anything to add on.

96
00:04:19,327 --> 00:04:20,749
So now let's us talk about

97
00:04:20,782 --> 00:04:24,191
how to prevent cracked soap tops or Soap Volcano.

98
00:04:24,703 --> 00:04:26,495
There are 6 points to share with you:

99
00:04:26,751 --> 00:04:30,591
Number 1: Keep the temperature of the mixture of lye solutions and oils around 30 degree celsius.

100
00:04:30,847 --> 00:04:32,833
Slight difference in temperature should be fine,

101
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:35,207
but if you are making household soap,

102
00:04:35,207 --> 00:04:37,679
it is best to keep the temperature below 30 degree celsius.

103
00:04:38,015 --> 00:04:40,646
Number 2: choose a less insulating mold.

104
00:04:40,646 --> 00:04:42,623
For instance, silicone molds with thinner walls

105
00:04:42,879 --> 00:04:44,671
or non-wood loaf mold.

106
00:04:45,439 --> 00:04:49,535
Number 3: you can choose not to insulate your newly-molded soap during the summer

107
00:04:49,791 --> 00:04:52,351
and put it at a dry and cool place if needed.

108
00:04:52,863 --> 00:04:53,452
Number 4:

109
00:04:53,452 --> 00:04:55,976
Avoid using naturally heat-producing additives,

110
00:04:55,976 --> 00:04:57,727
the ones we mentioned previously,

111
00:04:57,983 --> 00:04:59,263
those ingredients that contain protein,

112
00:04:59,519 --> 00:05:00,019
sugar,

113
00:05:00,019 --> 00:05:01,567
and alcohol,

114
00:05:01,823 --> 00:05:03,615
as well as some essential oils or fragrance oils.

115
00:05:03,871 --> 00:05:06,175
Number 5: increase the ratio of water

116
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:08,223
or increase the ratio of soft oils.

117
00:05:08,479 --> 00:05:11,115
When the amount of water increases, the saponification process will get slower

118
00:05:11,115 --> 00:05:13,599
and the heating process will also become slower,

119
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,391
thus reducing the likelihood of cracking.

120
00:05:15,647 --> 00:05:18,403
However, the soap will get overly soft if you add too much water.

121
00:05:18,403 --> 00:05:20,337
Please take this into consideration as well.

122
00:05:20,637 --> 00:05:22,047
But if you increase the ratio of soft oils,

123
00:05:22,303 --> 00:05:23,583
the soap will not be too hardened,

124
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:25,119
and it will not crack easily.

125
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:25,875
Number 6:

126
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:28,502
If you are making handmade soap with high proportion of coconut oil,

127
00:05:28,569 --> 00:05:30,239
for instance, coconut oil household soap.

128
00:05:30,369 --> 00:05:31,519
Then you can consider

129
00:05:31,669 --> 00:05:33,055
cooling the soap using electronic fan.

130
00:05:33,235 --> 00:05:36,334
Or you can put the soap into the fridge to help it cool down.

131
00:05:36,401 --> 00:05:38,734
It's the compartment of the fridge where you put your fruits and vegetables,

132
00:05:38,934 --> 00:05:39,967
please take note!

133
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:43,039
The example I am giving here is the handmade soap with high proportion of coconut oil

134
00:05:43,295 --> 00:05:46,879
which means not all handmade soaps are suitable to be placed into fridge for cooling.

135
00:05:47,391 --> 00:05:49,183
For instance,

136
00:05:49,439 --> 00:05:52,264
if the proportion of coconut oil is around 80% to 100% in a soap,

137
00:05:52,331 --> 00:05:53,535
then the proportion is considered high.

138
00:05:53,791 --> 00:05:55,583
Among all the handmade soap recipes,

139
00:05:55,839 --> 00:05:57,375
the coconut oil recipe

140
00:05:57,631 --> 00:06:00,191
is most likely to cause cracked tops or Soap Volcano.

141
00:06:00,703 --> 00:06:04,695
Coconut oil is considered a hard oil which induces fast saponification and speeds up the heating process.

142
00:06:04,762 --> 00:06:07,615
If you are making a 100% coconut oil household soap,

143
00:06:07,871 --> 00:06:09,663
the recipe does not contain soft oil at all.

144
00:06:10,175 --> 00:06:12,991
And if you use a mold with good thermal insulating properties...

145
00:06:21,951 --> 00:06:24,706
You might think that it's weird

146
00:06:24,706 --> 00:06:25,924
to put soap into the fridge for cooling,

147
00:06:25,991 --> 00:06:27,839
